  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "M&E Resident Technical Officer (RTO)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Qualification:</strong></p><ul><li>Possess a Diploma from a Polytechnic or BCA Academy or relevant qualifications.</li><li>Possess a certificate in Building Construction Supervisors Safety (BCSS) Course.</li><li>Accredited with the Joint Accreditation Committee of the Institute of Engineers Singapore and the Association of Consulting Engineers.</li></ul><p><strong>Experience:</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum 10 years relevant site experience as an RTO in the supervision of building M&E Services, especially Hotel and Residential projects.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Conversant in contract administration with Public Service Sector Conditions of Contract, conversant with statutory requirements, site management, quality control procedures, systems testing & commissioning and submission of progress reports.</li><li>Conversant in M&E design, specifications, site installation, services coordination, code of practice, Authority inspection and handing over.</li><li>Must be willing to do overtime or shift work.</li><li>Working hours will be <u><strong>6 days per week</strong></u> from 8am to 6pm.</li></ul><p><strong>Site Location:</strong></p><ul><li>Singapore Central Area</li></ul><p><strong>Expected Commencement Date:</strong></p><ul><li>March 2026</li></ul>",
